{'reasoning': "The cage internal size of 350x350x700mm implies a bounding box for the structure of 370x370x720mm (assuming 10mm bars outside the void). To fit the 400x400x50mm build volume, the vertical structure is sliced into layers. A 'Base' part (10mm frame + 40mm stubs) and 'Middle' parts (5mm frame + 40mm stubs) are designed. The 'Middle' parts are stacked in pairs (one inverted, one upright) to form 10mm frames and 80mm gaps (approx 78.75mm). Total 8 gaps are needed to reach 720mm height. The parts feature self-aligning hermaphroditic connectors on the intermediate bars and holes for M6 rods in the corners.", 'parts': [{'fileContents': 'module part(frame_h) {
    L = 39.375;
    centers = [-180, -90, 0, 90, 180];
    difference() {
        union() {
            // Frame
            for(x=centers) translate([x, 0, frame_h/2]) cube([10, 370, frame_h], center=true);
            for(y=centers) translate([0, y, frame_h/2]) cube([370, 10, frame_h], center=true);
            // Stubs
            for(x=centers) for(y=centers) {
                translate([x, y, frame_h + L/2]) cube([10, 10, L], center=true);
                // Connector Male (skip corners)
                if (abs(x)!=180 || abs(y)!=180) {
                     translate([x, y-2.5, frame_h + L + 1]) 
                     cylinder(r1=4, r2=2, h=2, $fn=4);
                }
            }
        }
        // Connector Female (skip corners)
        for(x=centers) for(y=centers) if (abs(x)!=180 || abs(y)!=180) {
             translate([x, y+2.5, frame_h + L - 1]) 
             cylinder(r1=2, r2=4, h=2.1, $fn=4);
        }
        // Rod Holes (Corners only)
        for(x=[-180, 180]) for(y=[-180, 180]) {
            translate([x, y, -1]) cylinder(r=3.5, h=200, $fn=20);
        }
    }
}
